  (for example, directories that contain their own LICENSE file).
- "You" means any individual or legal entity using the Work.
- "Commercial or Remunerated Use" means any use that is directly or indirectly
  intended for, results in, or is connected to monetary compensation or other
  economic advantage (including sales, paid access, paid services, sponsorship,
  monetized content, paid hosting, paid integration, consulting billed specifically
  for delivering/using this Work, or bundling with a paid product or service).
- "Corresponding Source" means the complete, buildable source code for the Work
  or derivative, including scripts/config needed to build and run it.
- "Public Deployment" includes running the Work (or a derivative) for users
  over a network (e.g., public Minecraft server, hosted API, SaaS), where users
  can interact with it.

